      <hedline>
        <hl1>BRAZIL DECISION ON BENEFITS POSTPONED</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Jennifer L. Rich</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Rich, Jennifer L</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Brazilian Supreme Court postpones widely anticipated decision that could force government to pay up to $30 billion in back benefits to contributors to national workers' fund; government has been accused of shortchinging contributors from 1987 to 1991, during period of financial crisis (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Supreme Court of Brazil postponed until next Thursday a widely awaited decision that could force the government to pay up to $30 billion in back benefits to contributors to the national workers' fund. The government has been accused of short-changing contributors to the fund from 1987 to 1991, during a period of financial crisis. Only three of the 60,000 cases pending have reached the Supreme Court, which could set a precedent with the decision.</p>
        <p>Jennifer L. Rich</p>
      </block>
